{
  "info": {
    "name": "HireRise — Admin CMS Dataset Ingestion",
    "description": "Complete test suite for the Admin CMS duplicate-prevention endpoints.\n\n## Setup\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable to your server (default: http://localhost:3000)\n2. Set the `adminToken` variable to a valid Firebase ID token for an admin user.\n   - Run `node get-firebase-token.mjs` from the project root to get one, or\n   - Use the Firebase Console → Authentication → copy a user's token.\n3. Run the **🔧 Health Check** request first to confirm the server is up.\n4. Run folders top-to-bottom — later tests reference IDs created by earlier ones.\n\n## Duplicate Prevention Behaviour\n- Creating the same skill twice returns **409 DUPLICATE_RECORD**\n- Names are normalized before comparison: 'JavaScript', 'javascript', 'java-script' all conflict\n- Roles are unique per job family: 'Director' in engineering ≠ 'Director' in product\n- Bulk import returns **207 Multi-Status** when some rows pass and some are duplicates",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",    "value": "http://localhost:3000",  "type": "string" },
    { "key": "apiPrefix",  "value": "/api/v1",                "type": "string" },
    { "key": "adminToken", "value": "PASTE_YOUR_FIREBASE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "skillId",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "roleId",     "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "jobFamilyId","value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔧 Health Check",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/health",
        "description": "Confirm the server is running before running any CMS tests."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Server is healthy', () => {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('healthy');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📁 Skills",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "✅ Create skill — JavaScript",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/admin/cms/skills",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n  \"category\": \"language\",\n  \"description\": \"High-level interpreted programming language\",\n  \"aliases\": [\"JS\", \"ECMAScript\"],\n  \"demandScore\": 95\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('success flag is true', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('skill has an id', () => {",
                  "  const id = pm.response.json().data?.id || pm.response.json().data?.skillId;",
                  "  pm.expect(id).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('skillId', id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved skillId:', id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "❌ Duplicate skill — same name exact case",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/admin/cms/skills",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n  \"category\": \"language\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('409 Conflict for exact duplicate', () => pm.response.to.have.status(409));",
                  "pm.test('error code is DUPLICATE_RECORD', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.success).to.be.false;",
                  "  pm.expect(body.error?.code || body.errorCode).to.eql('DUPLICATE_RECORD');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "❌ Duplicate skill — lowercase variant",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/admin/cms/skills",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"javascript\",\n  \"category\": \"language\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('409 Conflict — normalised name collision', () => pm.response.to.have.status(409));",
                  "pm.test('error code is DUPLICATE_RECORD', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().error?.code || pm.response.json().errorCode).to.eql('DUPLICATE_RECORD');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "❌ Duplicate skill — punctuation variant (java-script)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/admin/cms/skills",
